{
	"info": {
		"_postman_id": "ansible-inspec-api-collection",
		"name": "Ansible-InSpec API",
		"description": "Complete API collection for ansible-inspec server - enterprise compliance testing with Ansible and InSpec integration.\n\n## Getting Started\n\n1. **Set Collection Variables**: Configure `baseUrl` (e.g., `https://ansible-inspec.tripleseven.cloud` or `http://localhost:8080`)\n2. **Authenticate**: Run \"Password Login\" request to get JWT token (automatically saved)\n3. **Explore Endpoints**: Try health check, job templates, jobs, and VCS management\n\n## Authentication\n\nThe API uses JWT (JSON Web Tokens) for authentication. After successful login, the token is automatically saved to the `authToken` collection variable and included in subsequent requests.\n\n## Admin Credentials\n\nDefault admin credentials (configure via environment variables):\n- **Username**: admin\n- **Password**: Set via `ADMIN_PASSWORD` env var\n- **Email**: Set via `ADMIN_EMAIL` env var\n\n## Environment Variables\n\n- `baseUrl`: API server base URL (default: http://localhost:8080)\n- `authToken`: JWT token (automatically set after login)\n- `username`: Login username (default: admin)\n- `password`: Login password (set your admin password)",
		"schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json",
		"_exporter_id": "ansible-inspec"
	},
	"item": [
		{
			"name": "Authentication",
			"description": "Authentication endpoints for password-based and Azure AD login",
			"item": [
				{
					"name": "Password Login",
					"event": [
						{
							"listen": "test",
							"script": {
								"exec": [
									"// Save access token to collection variable",
									"if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
									"    const response = pm.response.json();",
									"    if (response.access_token) {",
									"        pm.collectionVariables.set('authToken', response.access_token);",
									"        console.log('✓ Auth token saved successfully');",
									"        pm.test('Login successful', function() {",
									"            pm.expect(response).to.have.property('access_token');",
									"            pm.expect(response).to.have.property('token_type', 'bearer');",
									"        });",
									"    }",
									"} else {",
									"    pm.test('Login failed', function() {",
									"        pm.response.to.have.status(401);",
									"    });",
									"}"
								],
								"type": "text/javascript"
							}
						}
					],
					"request": {
						"method": "POST",
						"header": [
							{
								"key": "Content-Type",
								"value": "application/json"
							}
						],
						"body": {
							"mode": "raw",
							"raw": "{\n    \"username\": \"{{username}}\",\n    \"password\": \"{{password}}\"\n}"
						},
						"url": {
							"raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/auth/password-login",
							"host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
							"path": ["api", "v1", "auth", "password-login"]
						},
						"description": "Login with username and password. Returns JWT token for authentication.\n\n**Request Body**:\n- `username`: User's username\n- `password`: User's password\n\n**Response**:\n- `access_token`: JWT token (use in Authorization header)\n- `token_type`: Token type (bearer)\n- `user_id`: User ID\n- `username`: Username\n- `roles`: User roles (e.g., [\"admin\"])"
					},
					"response": []
				},
				{
					"name": "Get Current User",
					"event": [
						{
							"listen": "test",
							"script": {
								"exec": [
									"pm.test('Status code is 200', function() {",
									"    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
									"});",
									"",
									"pm.test('User info returned', function() {",
									"    const response = pm.response.json();",
									"    pm.expect(response).to.have.property('username');",
									"    pm.expect(response).to.have.property('email');",
									"    pm.expect(response).to.have.property('roles');",
									"});"
								],
								"type": "text/javascript"
							}
						}
					],
					"request": {
						"method": "GET",
						"header": [
							{
								"key": "Authorization",
								"value": "Bearer {{authToken}}",
								"type": "text"
							}
						],
						"url": {
							"raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/auth/me",
							"host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
							"path": ["api", "v1", "auth", "me"]
						},
						"description": "Get current authenticated user information.\n\n**Requires**: Valid JWT token\n\n**Response**:\n- `id`: User ID\n- `username`: Username\n- `email`: Email address\n- `name`: Full name\n- `roles`: User roles array\n- `tenant_id`: Tenant ID (if Azure AD)"
					},
					"response": []
				},
				{
					"name": "Azure AD Login",
					"request": {
						"method": "GET",
						"header": [],
						"url": {
							"raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/auth/login",
							"host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
							"path": ["api", "v1", "auth", "login"]
						},
						"description": "Initiate Azure AD OAuth login flow. Redirects to Microsoft login page.\n\n**Note**: This endpoint is for browser-based authentication. For API testing, use password login instead."
					},
					"response": []
				},
				{
					"name": "Logout",
					"request": {
						"method": "POST",
						"header": [
							{
								"key": "Authorization",
								"value": "Bearer {{authToken}}",
								"type": "text"
							}
						],
						"url": {
							"raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/auth/logout",
							"host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
							"path": ["api", "v1", "auth", "logout"]
						},
						"description": "Logout and invalidate session.\n\n**Requires**: Valid JWT token"
					},
					"response": []
				}
			]
		},
		{
			"name": "Job Templates",
			"description": "Job template management - create, list, update, delete, and launch compliance testing jobs",
			"item": [
				{
					"name": "List Job Templates",
					"event": [
						{
							"listen": "test",
							"script": {
								"exec": [
									"pm.test('Status code is 200', function() {",
									"    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
									"});",
									"",
									"pm.test('Response has results array', function() {",
									"    const response = pm.response.json();",
									"    pm.expect(response).to.have.property('results');",
									"    pm.expect(response).to.have.property('count');",
									"});"
								],
								"type": "text/javascript"
							}
						}
					],
					"request": {
						"method": "GET",
						"header": [
							{
								"key": "Authorization",
								"value": "Bearer {{authToken}}",
								"type": "text"
							}
						],
						"url": {
							"raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/job-templates",
							"host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
							"path": ["api", "v1", "job-templates"]
						},
						"description": "List all job templates.\n\n**Requires**: Valid JWT token\n\n**Response**:\n- `count`: Total number of templates\n- `results`: Array of job template objects"
					},
					"response": []
				},
				{
					"name": "Create Job Template",
					"event": [
						{
							"listen": "test",
							"script": {
								"exec": [
									"pm.test('Status code is 201', function() {",
									"    pm.response.to.have.status(201);",
									"});",
									"",
									"if (pm.response.code === 201) {",
									"    const response = pm.response.json();",
									"    pm.collectionVariables.set('templateId', response.id);",
									"    console.log('✓ Template ID saved: ' + response.id);",
									"}"
								],
								"type": "text/javascript"
							}
						}
					],
					"request": {
						"method": "POST",
						"header": [
							{
								"key": "Authorization",
								"value": "Bearer {{authToken}}",
								"type": "text"
							},
							{
								"key": "Content-Type",
								"value": "application/json"
							}
						],
						"body": {
							"mode": "raw",
							"raw": "{\n    \"name\": \"Linux Security Baseline\",\n    \"description\": \"DevSec Linux baseline security compliance checks\",\n    \"profile\": \"dev-sec/linux-baseline\",\n    \"extra_vars\": {\n        \"reporter\": \"json\",\n        \"target\": \"ssh://user@host\"\n    },\n    \"vcs_sync\": false\n}"
						},
						"url": {
							"raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/job-templates",
							"host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
							"path": ["api", "v1", "job-templates"]
						},
						"description": "Create a new job template.\n\n**Request Body**:\n- `name`: Template name (required)\n- `description`: Template description\n- `profile`: InSpec profile name or Chef Supermarket path (required)\n- `extra_vars`: Additional variables (JSON object)\n- `vcs_repo_id`: VCS repository ID (optional)\n- `vcs_path`: Path in VCS repository (optional)\n- `vcs_sync`: Sync from VCS before running (default: false)\n\n**Response**: Created template object with ID"
					},
					"response": []
				},
				{
					"name": "Get Job Template",
					"request": {
						"method": "GET",
						"header": [
							{
								"key": "Authorization",
								"value": "Bearer {{authToken}}",
								"type": "text"
							}
						],
						"url": {
							"raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/job-templates/{{templateId}}",
							"host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
							"path": ["api", "v1", "job-templates", "{{templateId}}"]
						},
						"description": "Get a specific job template by ID.\n\n**Requires**: Valid JWT token\n\n**Path Parameter**: `template_id`"
					},
					"response": []
				},
				{
					"name": "Update Job Template",
					"request": {
						"method": "PUT",
						"header": [
							{
								"key": "Authorization",
								"value": "Bearer {{authToken}}",
								"type": "text"
							},
							{
								"key": "Content-Type",
								"value": "application/json"
							}
						],
						"body": {
							"mode": "raw",
							"raw": "{\n    \"description\": \"Updated: DevSec Linux baseline security compliance checks with custom settings\",\n    \"extra_vars\": {\n        \"reporter\": \"json\",\n        \"target\": \"ssh://user@host\",\n        \"custom_setting\": \"value\"\n    }\n}"
						},
						"url": {
							"raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/job-templates/{{templateId}}",
							"host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
							"path": ["api", "v1", "job-templates", "{{templateId}}"]
						},
						"description": "Update an existing job template.\n\n**Request Body** (all fields optional):\n- `name`: Updated template name\n- `description`: Updated description\n- `profile`: Updated profile name\n- `extra_vars`: Updated variables\n\n**Path Parameter**: `template_id`"
					},
					"response": []
				},
				{
					"name": "Launch Job from Template",
					"event": [
						{
							"listen": "test",
							"script": {
								"exec": [
									"pm.test('Status code is 201', function() {",
									"    pm.response.to.have.status(201);",
									"});",
									"",
									"if (pm.response.code === 201) {",
									"    const response = pm.response.json();",
									"    pm.collectionVariables.set('jobId', response.id);",
									"    console.log('✓ Job ID saved: ' + response.id);",
									"}"
								],
								"type": "text/javascript"
							}
						}
					],
					"request": {
						"method": "POST",
						"header": [
							{
								"key": "Authorization",
								"value": "Bearer {{authToken}}",
								"type": "text"
							},
							{
								"key": "Content-Type",
								"value": "application/json"
							}
						],
						"body": {
							"mode": "raw",
							"raw": "{\n    \"target\": \"ssh://user@192.168.1.100\",\n    \"extra_vars\": {\n        \"custom_var\": \"value\"\n    }\n}"
						},
						"url": {
							"raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/job-templates/{{templateId}}/launch",
							"host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
							"path": ["api", "v1", "job-templates", "{{templateId}}", "launch"]
						},
						"description": "Launch a new job from a template.\n\n**Request Body**:\n- `target`: Target host/inventory (optional, can override template)\n- `extra_vars`: Additional variables (merged with template vars)\n\n**Path Parameter**: `template_id`\n\n**Response**: Created job object with status"
					},
					"response": []
				},
				{
					"name": "Delete Job Template",
					"request": {
						"method": "DELETE",
						"header": [
							{
								"key": "Authorization",
								"value": "Bearer {{authToken}}",
								"type": "text"
							}
						],
						"url": {
							"raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/job-templates/{{templateId}}",
							"host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
							"path": ["api", "v1", "job-templates", "{{templateId}}"]
						},
						"description": "Delete a job template.\n\n**Requires**: Valid JWT token\n\n**Path Parameter**: `template_id`\n\n**Response**: 204 No Content"
					},
					"response": []
				}
			]
		},
		{
			"name": "Jobs",
			"description": "Job execution and monitoring - create jobs, check status, view results",
			"item": [
				{
					"name": "List Jobs",
					"event": [
						{
							"listen": "test",
							"script": {
								"exec": [
									"pm.test('Status code is 200', function() {",
									"    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
									"});",
									"",
									"pm.test('Response has results array', function() {",
									"    const response = pm.response.json();",
									"    pm.expect(response).to.have.property('results');",
									"    pm.expect(response).to.have.property('count');",
									"});"
								],
								"type": "text/javascript"
							}
						}
					],
					"request": {
						"method": "GET",
						"header": [
							{
								"key": "Authorization",
								"value": "Bearer {{authToken}}",
								"type": "text"
							}
						],
						"url": {
							"raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/jobs?limit=20&skip=0",
							"host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
							"path": ["api", "v1", "jobs"],
							"query": [
								{
									"key": "limit",
									"value": "20",
									"description": "Number of results to return"
								},
								{
									"key": "skip",
									"value": "0",
									"description": "Number of results to skip (pagination)"
								}
							]
						},
						"description": "List all jobs with pagination.\n\n**Query Parameters**:\n- `limit`: Number of results (default: 20)\n- `skip`: Number to skip for pagination (default: 0)\n\n**Response**:\n- `count`: Total number of jobs\n- `results`: Array of job objects with status, results, timestamps"
					},
					"response": []
				},
				{
					"name": "Create Job",
					"event": [
						{
							"listen": "test",
							"script": {
								"exec": [
									"pm.test('Status code is 201', function() {",
									"    pm.response.to.have.status(201);",
									"});",
									"",
									"if (pm.response.code === 201) {",
									"    const response = pm.response.json();",
									"    pm.collectionVariables.set('jobId', response.id);",
									"    console.log('✓ Job ID saved: ' + response.id);",
									"}"
								],
								"type": "text/javascript"
							}
						}
					],
					"request": {
						"method": "POST",
						"header": [
							{
								"key": "Authorization",
								"value": "Bearer {{authToken}}",
								"type": "text"
							},
							{
								"key": "Content-Type",
								"value": "application/json"
							}
						],
						"body": {
							"mode": "raw",
							"raw": "{\n    \"template_id\": \"{{templateId}}\",\n    \"target\": \"ssh://user@192.168.1.100\",\n    \"extra_vars\": {\n        \"reporter\": \"json\"\n    }\n}"
						},
						"url": {
							"raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/jobs",
							"host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
							"path": ["api", "v1", "jobs"]
						},
						"description": "Create and launch a new job.\n\n**Request Body**:\n- `template_id`: Job template ID (required)\n- `target`: Target host/inventory (optional)\n- `extra_vars`: Additional variables (optional)\n\n**Response**: Created job object with status"
					},
					"response": []
				},
				{
					"name": "Get Job",
					"event": [
						{
							"listen": "test",
							"script": {
								"exec": [
									"pm.test('Status code is 200', function() {",
									"    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
									"});",
									"",
									"pm.test('Job has status', function() {",
									"    const response = pm.response.json();",
									"    pm.expect(response).to.have.property('status');",
									"    pm.expect(response).to.have.property('id');",
									"    console.log('Job status: ' + response.status);",
									"});"
								],
								"type": "text/javascript"
							}
						}
					],
					"request": {
						"method": "GET",
						"header": [
							{
								"key": "Authorization",
								"value": "Bearer {{authToken}}",
								"type": "text"
							}
						],
						"url": {
							"raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/jobs/{{jobId}}",
							"host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
							"path": ["api", "v1", "jobs", "{{jobId}}"]
						},
						"description": "Get job details including status and results.\n\n**Path Parameter**: `job_id`\n\n**Response**:\n- `id`: Job ID\n- `status`: Job status (pending, running, success, failed)\n- `results`: InSpec test results (JSON)\n- `created_at`: Creation timestamp\n- `started_at`: Start timestamp\n- `finished_at`: Completion timestamp"
					},
					"response": []
				}
			]
		},
		{
			"name": "VCS Credentials",
			"description": "VCS credential management for GitHub, GitLab, BitBucket integration",
			"item": [
				{
					"name": "List VCS Credentials",
					"request": {
						"method": "GET",
						"header": [
							{
								"key": "Authorization",
								"value": "Bearer {{authToken}}",
								"type": "text"
							}
						],
						"url": {
							"raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/vcs/credentials",
							"host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
							"path": ["api", "v1", "vcs", "credentials"]
						},
						"description": "List all VCS credentials.\n\n**Note**: Passwords and tokens are not returned for security.\n\n**Response**: Array of credential objects (without sensitive data)"
					},
					"response": []
				},
				{
					"name": "Create VCS Credential (Token)",
					"event": [
						{
							"listen": "test",
							"script": {
								"exec": [
									"pm.test('Status code is 201', function() {",
									"    pm.response.to.have.status(201);",
									"});",
									"",
									"if (pm.response.code === 201) {",
									"    const response = pm.response.json();",
									"    pm.collectionVariables.set('credentialId', response.id);",
									"    console.log('✓ Credential ID saved: ' + response.id);",
									"}"
								],
								"type": "text/javascript"
							}
						}
					],
					"request": {
						"method": "POST",
						"header": [
							{
								"key": "Authorization",
								"value": "Bearer {{authToken}}",
								"type": "text"
							},
							{
								"key": "Content-Type",
								"value": "application/json"
							}
						],
						"body": {
							"mode": "raw",
							"raw": "{\n    \"name\": \"GitHub Personal Access Token\",\n    \"vcs_type\": \"github\",\n    \"token\": \"ghp_your_github_token_here\",\n    \"repository_url\": \"https://github.com/your-org/your-repo\"\n}"
						},
						"url": {
							"raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/vcs/credentials",
							"host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
							"path": ["api", "v1", "vcs", "credentials"]
						},
						"description": "Create VCS credential with token authentication.\n\n**Request Body**:\n- `name`: Credential name (required)\n- `vcs_type`: Type (github, gitlab, bitbucket, git)\n- `token`: Personal access token (encrypted)\n- `repository_url`: Repository URL (optional)\n\n**Note**: Credentials are encrypted before storage."
					},
					"response": []
				},
				{
					"name": "Create VCS Credential (SSH Key)",
					"request": {
						"method": "POST",
						"header": [
							{
								"key": "Authorization",
								"value": "Bearer {{authToken}}",
								"type": "text"
							},
							{
								"key": "Content-Type",
								"value": "application/json"
							}
						],
						"body": {
							"mode": "raw",
							"raw": "{\n    \"name\": \"GitHub SSH Key\",\n    \"vcs_type\": \"github\",\n    \"ssh_private_key\": \"-----BEGIN OPENSSH PRIVATE KEY-----\\nYour private key here\\n-----END OPENSSH PRIVATE KEY-----\",\n    \"repository_url\": \"git@github.com:your-org/your-repo.git\"\n}"
						},
						"url": {
							"raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/vcs/credentials",
							"host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
							"path": ["api", "v1", "vcs", "credentials"]
						},
						"description": "Create VCS credential with SSH key authentication.\n\n**Request Body**:\n- `name`: Credential name (required)\n- `vcs_type`: Type (github, gitlab, bitbucket, git)\n- `ssh_private_key`: SSH private key (encrypted)\n- `repository_url`: Repository URL (optional)"
					},
					"response": []
				},
				{
					"name": "Create VCS Credential (Username/Password)",
					"request": {
						"method": "POST",
						"header": [
							{
								"key": "Authorization",
								"value": "Bearer {{authToken}}",
								"type": "text"
							},
							{
								"key": "Content-Type",
								"value": "application/json"
							}
						],
						"body": {
							"mode": "raw",
							"raw": "{\n    \"name\": \"GitLab Credentials\",\n    \"vcs_type\": \"gitlab\",\n    \"username\": \"your-username\",\n    \"password\": \"your-password\",\n    \"repository_url\": \"https://gitlab.com/your-org/your-repo\"\n}"
						},
						"url": {
							"raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/vcs/credentials",
							"host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
							"path": ["api", "v1", "vcs", "credentials"]
						},
						"description": "Create VCS credential with username/password authentication.\n\n**Request Body**:\n- `name`: Credential name (required)\n- `vcs_type`: Type (github, gitlab, bitbucket, git)\n- `username`: Username\n- `password`: Password (encrypted)\n- `repository_url`: Repository URL (optional)"
					},
					"response": []
				},
